Let’s be honest – who here doesn’t love sushi? I could eat it daily although I don’t need or want that much rice every week. Which is why this low-carb, 100% plant-based rainbow cucumber sushi is the perfect compromise! I’ve shared options similar in my story for years but this is awesome! By @alphafoodie

This rainbow cucumber sushi is not only 100% plant-based , but can be made in under 15 minutes and perfect for a healthy, delicious low-carb lunch or snack served alongside a delicious vegan avocado dip!

1 tbsp lemon juice
2 tbsp chives
¼ tsp salt
¼ tsp pepper
⠀
⠀

1 sweet potato
2 tbsp olive oil
1 tbsp fresh rosemary, chopped
1 tsp salt
1 tsp pepper
⠀

2 zucchinis

1 tbsp garlic powder
1 tbsp dried basil
1 tsp salt
1 tsp pepper
2 eggs
⠀

2 carrots

1 tsp pepper
⠀

1 tsp salt

2 eggs ⭐️
⠀

node.text:
Follow @bodysmartfitness for the best fitness tips! 
 
Healthy food doesn’t have to be boring. 
 
These always hit the spot and are a filling, nutrient dense, and “whatever diet you want to call it” friendly….by @shredhappens 
.
Which one of these would you choose?? Swipe right to see all of the options.
.
1.Air fried spice crusted salmon with medium boiled eggs, cukes, cherry hot peppers, green beans, and some hemp hearts.
.
2. Lamb with cucumber mint yogurt,walnuts, fresh herbs, and greens.
.
3. Spicy shrimp, Brussels sprouts, avocado and soft boiled eggs over greens.
.
4.Lemon garlic air fried salmon with avocado, cherry tomatos, eggs, and greens.
.
5.Lamb with power greens, fried halloumi, herbs, and tons of veggies.
.
I always start with a big base of greens (usually @josiesorganics arugula, baby lettuce mix, or spinach), add a protein (love @wholefoods salmon, shrimp, or lamb), add some healthy fats from avocados or nuts, and then add some yolky goodness and other veggies/toppings to keep things interesting.
.
All are also perfect meal prep options and hold up well in the fridge. Just add the avocado the day you plan to eat it.
.
.
.
#powerbowl #MealPrep #LowCarb #KetoDiet #Keto #Healthyfood #healthyrecipes #healthymeals #ketomeals #ketofood #ketogenicfood #ketocipes #lchf #lowcarbrecipes #ketomealprep #ketolife

node.text:
Follow @bodysmartfitness for the best fitness tips! 
 
Lemon Chicken And Asparagus Stir-Fry (Under 500 Calories) 🍗 
Full recipe below, send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣…By @buzzfeedtasty 
 
Ingredients (for 3 servings)
* ½ tablespoon olive oil
* 2 chicken breasts, sliced
* 1 teaspoon salt
* ½ teaspoon pepper
* 1 tablespoon garlic, minced
* 4 oz asparagus (100 g)
* ½ lemon, zested
* ½ lemon, juiced
* 3 tablespoons soy sauce
* lemon, zested, to garnish
* rice, to serve

Preparation
1. Season the chicken with the salt and pepper and fry with the olive oil. After a few minutes, add the garlic. 
 
2. Fry the chicken with the garlic for another few minutes, then add the asparagus, lemon zest, and lemon juice. 

3. Stir again, before mixing in the soy sauce. 
 
4. Serve with rice and sprinkle with lemon zest on top. 

5. Enjoy!
 
#chicken #healthycooking

🍟 🐠 EAT or PASS?! 
 
Mussels & Fries (Moules-frites)... Super easy, always delicious & more fun when cooked outside…By @primal_gourmet 
 
This one’s a riff on a classic Moules Marinières, but I personally prefer the flavour of leeks over celery, fish stock instead of white wine & usually leave out the heavy cream. I also add some chopped tomato at the end for a pop of colour. Served with the Oven Fries & some homemade mayo for dipping 👌
.
Some Notes:
1. Mussels need a bit of time to prep & clean but it's easy work & after that, things move quickly
2. IMPORTANT: clean the mussels very well before cooking (see recipe). Discard any that are not closed BEFORE cooking & any that remain closed AFTER cooking. Also discard any with broken shells
.
Ingredients:
* 2 pounds mussels
* Kosher salt
* 2 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil
* 2 leeks, thinly sliced
* 2 shallots, thinly sliced
* 4 cloves garlic, finely chopped
* 1 tablespoon grass-fed butter or ghee
* ¼ teaspoon freshly-cracked black pepper
* 2 cup fish or seafood stock (substitute white wine or vegetable stock)
* 1 large tomato, seeds removed & diced
* ¼ cup fresh parsley leaves, finely chopped
* 1 Recipe Oven Fries
 
Method:
1. Fill a large bowl with cold water, add the mussels & 2 tablespoons kosher salt. Move the mussels around to agitate & let sit for 15 minutes to purge any sand or dirt inside the shells. 
 
2. Rinse the mussels very well with cold water, scrub off any barnacles, & remove any beards between each shell. Discard any mussels with broken shells & those that do not close up when gently squeezed. Transfer to a bowl with clean ice water & set aside. 
 
3. Preheat a large pot over medium heat. Add the olive oil & heat until shimmering. Add the leeks & shallot & season with a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until slightly soft & translucent, around 6 minutes. Add the garlic & butter & cook, stirring, 60 seconds. Season with pepper & add the mussels. Toss to coat, add the fish stock & tomatoes & cover with a lid. Cook until the mussels have opened, around 6 minutes. Garnish with parsley & serve with fries. Enjoy immediately. 
 
#mussels #fish #seafood #fries #healthymeals

Garlic Veggie Rotini Pasta 🍝 
Full recipe below, send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣…By @buzzfeedtasty 

Ingredients (for 3 servings)
* 2 tablespoons oil
* 2 cups mushrooms (150 g), sliced
* 2 cups broccoli (500 g), chopped
* 4 cloves garlic, chopped
* 2 bell peppers, sliced
* 1 tablespoon dried oregano
* 2 teaspoons salt
* 2 teaspoons pepper
* 1 ¼ cups rotini pasta (250 g)

Preparation
1. Heat oil in a large pot over high heat. 
 
2. Cook mushrooms, broccoli, garlic, peppers, oregano, salt, and pepper until the vegetables are tender. 
 
3. Add in the pasta and stir until evenly mixed. 
 
4. Enjoy!

Follow @laura_lambe to learn how to transform your physique and still eat your favourite foods. 
 
5-minute veggie packed creamy pasta sauce 🥦🥬💚 …By @strengthandsalad
 
This uses broccoli, peas and rocket for a hit of vitamin c, vitamin a, manganese, potassium, and b vitamins, making it super nutrient rich and amazing for our gut health 🙌.
⠀ 
(serves 2-3)
- 2 cups broccoli florets
- 1 packed cup leafy greens (i used rocket but you could also use spinach, kale, salad leaves, whatever you have to hand)
- 1/2 cup frozen or fresh peas
- 1 cup cashews
- 1.5 cups pasta water
- 1 heaped tsp flaky sea salt
- 1 large garlic clove
- 1/4 cup nutritional yeast (optional, but good for plant protein)
⠀ 
steam the florets for a few minutes (you can also roast or boil them if you prefer) until slightly soft but still vibrant green. drain and add everything to a blender. blend for 1-2 minutes until silky smooth (add more pasta water if necessary). pour generously over gluten free pasta and top with cracked pepper, lemon juice, and sweet cherry tomatoes. enjoy friends! 
 
#pasta #futhealth #healthyneal #herbs #brocolli #cashews #homecookedmeal #homecooked #homecookedfood #mealplan #dietplan

Pesto Turkey Pinwheels 🥪 
Full recipe below, send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣…By @buzzfeedtasty 

Ingredients (for 10 servings)
2 large flour tortillas
¼ cup pesto (55 g), divided
1 cup cherry tomato (200 g), halved, divided
½ lb turkey (225 g), sliced, divided
2 oz baby spinach (55 g), divided
4 slices provolone cheese, halved

Preparation
Warm the tortillas in the microwave in 30-second intervals, until flexible. Transfer to a clean work surface. 
 
Spread on half the pesto on each tortilla.
Divide the tomatoes, turkey, spinach, and provolone between the tortillas. 
 
Wrap the tortillas tightly in plastic wrap and rest for 30 minutes. 
 
Stick 6 toothpicks 1-inch (2.5 cm) apart into the wraps along the seam. 
 
Slice between the toothpicks and serve.
Enjoy!

Follow @bodysmartfitness for the best fitness tips! 
 
Salmon Meal Prep for Two 🤤 
Full recipe below, send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣…By @buzzfeedtasty 
 
Ingredients
for 4 servings
BALSAMIC SOY SALMON
½ cup soy sauce (120 mL)
½ cup balsamic vinegar (120 mL)
¼ cup olive oil (60 mL)
2 cloves garlic, minced
12 oz salmon (345 g), 2 fillets 
 
GARLIC PAPRIKA
1 teaspoon paprika
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1 teaspoon onion powder
1 teaspoon salt
½ teaspoon pepper
12 oz salmon (345 g), 2 fillets 
 
VEGETABLES
1 large carrot, thinly sliced on bias
5 oz green beans (140 g), ends trimmed
5 oz asparagus (140 g), ends trimmed, chopped
1 medium yellow squash, chopped
olive oil, to taste
salt, to taste
pepper, to taste

Preparation
In a square baking dish, combine the soy sauce, balsamic vinegar, oil, and garlic, and whisk to combine. 
 
Put 2 of the salmon fillets in the soy and balsamic mixture, making sure all sides are coated. 
 
Transfer to the refrigerator, marinading for 30 minutes to 2 hours. 
 
Preheat oven to 450˚F (230˚C). 
 
In a small bowl, mix together the paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper. 
 
Evenly coat the remaining 2 salmon filets with the spice rub. 
 
Place the salmon and vegetables on a parchment paper-lined baking tray. 
 
Drizzle olive oil and sprinkle salt and pepper to taste over the vegetables. 
 
Bake for 11 minutes per inch (2.5 cm) of salmon thickness. 

Divide the salmon and vegetables into 4 containers, mix and matching the vegetables to your liking. 
 
Refrigerate for up to 3 days. 
 
Enjoy!
